<paragraph id="8BA636A09E72745DFA61284AD32ADD04" blockId="36.[264,788,1062,1088]" box="[264,788,1062,1088]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<heading id="D0EE81CC9E72745DFA61284AD32ADD04" bold="true" box="[264,788,1062,1088]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B96DEAB29E72745DFA61284AD32ADD04" bold="true" box="[264,788,1062,1088]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B96DEAB29E72745DFA61284AD223DD04" bold="true" box="[264,541,1062,1088]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Microvescia 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D239E72745DFACB284AD223DD04" authority="Wygodzinsky, 1943" authorityName="Wygodzinsky" authorityYear="1943" box="[418,541,1062,1088]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Microlestria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Hemiptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="costalimai">costalimai</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF884B519E72745DF94D284AD32ADD04" author="Wygodzinsky" box="[548,788,1062,1088]" pageId="36" pageNumber="46" refString="Wygodzinsky, P. (1943) Contribuicao ao conhecimento da subfamilia Vesciinae (Hemiptera, Reduviidae). Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 3, 203 - 223." type="journal article" year="1943">
Wygodzinsky, 
<number id="3DD124879E72745DF9B3284AD32ADD04" box="[730,788,1062,1088]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="1943.0">1943</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA636A09E72745DFA61281DD1BEDFA7" blockId="36.[264,1324,1137,1883]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
This genus and species were described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF884B519E72745DF993281DD3CFDDCF" author="Wygodzinsky" box="[762,1009,1137,1163]" pageId="36" pageNumber="46" refString="Wygodzinsky, P. (1943) Contribuicao ao conhecimento da subfamilia Vesciinae (Hemiptera, Reduviidae). Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 3, 203 - 223." type="journal article" year="1943">
Wygodzinsky (
<number id="3DD124879E72745DF8C2281DD3D6DDCF" box="[939,1000,1137,1163]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="1943.0">1943</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
from a single female from “Rio Araguaia, Goiaz,” 
<collectingCountry id="F30E76309E72745DF94E28F5D24DDDF7" box="[551,627,1177,1203]" name="Brazil" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. It has been recorded additionally from 
<collectingCountry id="F30E76309E72745DFF3828F5D4A5DDF7" box="[1105,1179,1177,1203]" name="Brazil" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, from Nova Teutonia (Santa Catarina) (
<bibRefCitation id="EF884B519E72745DF93A28ADD35FDD9F" author="Drake" box="[595,865,1217,1243]" pageId="36" pageNumber="43" refString="Drake, C. J. &amp; Harris, H. M. (1945) Concerning the subfamily &quot; Vesciinae &quot; (Hemiptera, Reduviidae). Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 5, 155 - 156." type="journal article" year="1945">
Drake &amp; Harris 
<number id="3DD124879E72745DF84B28ADD35FDD9F" box="[802,865,1217,1243]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="1945.0">1945</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D239E72745DF81328ADD41FDD9E" box="[890,1057,1217,1242]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Microlestria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Hemiptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="costalimai">
<emphasis id="B96DEAB29E72745DF81328ADD41FDD9E" box="[890,1057,1217,1242]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">M. costalimai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has never been cited again in the literature (
<bibRefCitation id="EF884B519E72745DF9482885D2CDDC47" author="Maldonado" box="[545,755,1257,1283]" pageId="36" pageNumber="42" refString="Carpintero, D. J. &amp; Maldonado C., J. (1990) Contributions to the knowledge of American Ectrichodiinae II. Notes about Rhiginia and Pothea (Hemiptera: Reduviidae). Journal of Agriculture of the University of Puerto Rico, 74, 449 - 456." type="journal article" year="1990">
Maldonado 
<number id="3DD124879E72745DF9DD2885D2CDDC47" box="[692,755,1257,1283]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="1990.0">1990</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Here, a specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="F30E76309E72745DFF442885D44BDC47" box="[1069,1141,1257,1283]" name="Brazil" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Brazil</collectingCountry>
was examined (
<figureCitation id="13222A259E72745DFA78297DD1A5DC6F" box="[273,411,1297,1323]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 52 – 60" captionStart-1="FIGURES 61 – 66" captionStartId-0="33.[264,382,1619,1643]" captionStartId-1="38.[264,382,1116,1140]" captionTargetBox-0="[349,1269,336,1583]" captionTargetBox-1="[348,1274,320,1082]" captionTargetId-0="figure@33.[312,1275,321,1593]" captionTargetId-1="figure@38.[312,1275,312,1089]" captionTargetPageId-0="33" captionTargetPageId-1="38" captionText-0="FIGURES 52 – 60. Dorsal and lateral views of Reduviidae species. 52, Rasahus costaricensis, late instar nymph; 53, Rasahus rufiventris; 54, Microlestria laevis; 55, Opisthacidius mexicanus; 56, Volesus nigripennis, dorsal view; 57, V. nigripennis, lateral view; 58, Kodormus bruneosus; 59, Ocrioessa lobuliventris; 60, Microvescia costalimai, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1 mm (52, 54, 60); 3 mm (53); 4 mm (55 ­ 59)." captionText-1="FIGURES 61 – 66. Dorsal and lateral views of Reduviidae species. 61, M. costalimai, lateral view. 62, Mirambulus morio, dorsal view; 63, lateral view; 64, Pessoaia limai; 65, Vescia spicula; 66, Ves cia sp., brachypterous female. Scale bar: 1 mm (61); 2 mm (64 ­ 66); 3 mm (62, 63)." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/171465/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/171466/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
Figs. 
<number id="3DD124879E72745DFA3A297DD1A5DC6F" box="[339,411,1297,1323]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="60.5" valueMax="61.0" valueMin="60.0">60­61</number>
</figureCitation>
), also from “Rio Araguaia,” but in the state of Mato Grosso, and hence a new state record. In Wygodzinsky’s habitus drawing (
<number id="3DD124879E72745DF8022955D397DC17" box="[875,937,1337,1363]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="1943.0">1943</number>
, fig. 
<number id="3DD124879E72745DF8982955D42FDC17" box="[1009,1041,1337,1363]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="86.0">86</number>
), he did not show the prolongation on the fore tibiae, although he mentioned it in the description and illustrated it in figures 
<number id="3DD124879E72745DFAF529E5D187DCE7" box="[412,441,1417,1443]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="93.0">93</number>
and 
<number id="3DD124879E72745DFA9F29E5D22DDCE7" box="[502,531,1417,1443]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="94.0">94</number>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF884B519E72745DF94D29E5D32EDCE7" author="Wygodzinsky" box="[548,784,1417,1443]" pageId="36" pageNumber="46" refString="Wygodzinsky, P. (1943) Contribuicao ao conhecimento da subfamilia Vesciinae (Hemiptera, Reduviidae). Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 3, 203 - 223." type="journal article" year="1943">
Wygodzinsky 
<number id="3DD124879E72745DF9B829E5D32EDCE7" box="[721,784,1417,1443]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="1943.0">1943</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). In the female examined here, this character was confirmed. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF884B519E72745DFABB29DDD338DC8F" author="China" box="[466,774,1457,1483]" pageId="36" pageNumber="42" refString="China, W. E. &amp; Usinger, R. L. (1948) A new species of Chopardita Villiers from the Anglo-Egyptian Sudan with notes on the subfamily Vesciinae (Hemiptera-Reduviidae). The Annals and Magazine of Natural History, ser. 12, 1, 598 - 604." type="journal article" year="1948">
<collectingCountry id="F30E76309E72745DFABB29DDD226DC8F" box="[466,536,1457,1483]" name="China" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">China</collectingCountry>
&amp; Usinger (
<number id="3DD124879E72745DF9A929DDD2C3DC8F" box="[704,765,1457,1483]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="1948.0">1948</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
erroneously stated –without examining any specimens– that 
<emphasis id="B96DEAB29E72745DFABC29B5D25BDCB6" box="[469,613,1497,1522]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Microvescia</emphasis>
has “the front tibiae straight and simple at their apices,” based on 
<bibRefCitation id="EF884B519E72745DFAE02A6DD2B3DF5F" author="Wygodzinsky" box="[393,653,1537,1563]" pageId="36" pageNumber="46" refString="Wygodzinsky, P. (1943) Contribuicao ao conhecimento da subfamilia Vesciinae (Hemiptera, Reduviidae). Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 3, 203 - 223." type="journal article" year="1943">
Wygodzinsky (
<number id="3DD124879E72745DF92D2A6DD2BADF5F" box="[580,644,1537,1563]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="1943.0">1943</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Nevertheless, this is not an accurate translation of Wygodzinsky statement (
<number id="3DD124879E72745DF9502A45D249DF07" box="[569,631,1577,1603]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="1943.0">1943</number>
, pg. 
<number id="3DD124879E72745DF9DE2A45D2D6DF07" box="[695,744,1577,1603]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="220.0">220</number>
): “Tibia anterior ventralmente sem espinhos ou saliências; proceso distal liso, sem pêlos,” which can be translated as “Anterior tibiae ventrally without spines or protuberances; distal process smooth, without hairs” (my translation). 
<bibRefCitation id="EF884B519E72745DFAF62ACDD2F9DFFF" author="China" box="[415,711,1697,1723]" pageId="36" pageNumber="42" refString="China, W. E. &amp; Usinger, R. L. (1948) A new species of Chopardita Villiers from the Anglo-Egyptian Sudan with notes on the subfamily Vesciinae (Hemiptera-Reduviidae). The Annals and Magazine of Natural History, ser. 12, 1, 598 - 604." type="journal article" year="1948">
<collectingCountry id="F30E76309E72745DFAF62ACDD1DBDFFF" box="[415,485,1697,1723]" name="China" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">China</collectingCountry>
&amp; Usinger (
<number id="3DD124879E72745DF9E82ACDD280DFFF" box="[641,702,1697,1723]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="1948.0">1948</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
used this observation to question the status of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D239E72745DFA612AA5D142DFA7" box="[264,380,1737,1763]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Vesciinae">Vesciinae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
